gebra/Notation/Defs.html#Star.star\">star</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.cons\">,</a>     <span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <span class=\"fn\">A</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Units/Defs.html#IsUnit\">IsUnit</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Notation/Defs.html#Star.star\">star</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span></span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.cons\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Units/Defs.html#IsUnit\">IsUnit</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.cons\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Star/SelfAdjoint.html#IsSelfAdjoint\">IsSelfAdjoint</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">∀ <span class=\"fn\">x</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Spectrum/Basic.html#spectrum\">spectrum</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span>, <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.cons\">]</a>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/List/TFAE.html#List.TFAE\">TFAE</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For an element `a` in a C⋆-algebra, TFAE:\n1. `a` is strictly positive,\n2. `sqrt a` is strictly positive and `a = sqrt a * sqrt a`,\n3. `sqrt a` is invertible and `a = sqrt a * sqrt a`,\n4. `a = b * b` for some strictly positive `b`,\n5. `a = b * b` for some self-adjoint and invertible `b`,\n6. `a = star b * b` for some invertible `b`,\n7. `a = b * star b` for some invertible `b`,\n8. `0 ≤ a` and `a` is invertible,\n9. `a` is self-adjoint and has positive spectrum. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/SpecialFunctions/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus/Rpow/Basic.html#CStarAlgebra.isStrictlyPositive_TFAE","kind":"theorem","line":736,"name":"CStarAlgebra.isStrictlyPositive_TFAE","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/SpecialFunctions/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus/Rpow/Basic.lean#L736-L767"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/SpecialFunctions/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus/Rpow/Basic.html#IsStrictlyPositive.rpow\"><span class=\"name\">IsStrictlyPositive</span>.<span class=\"name\">rpow</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Defs/PartialOrder.html#PartialOrder\">PartialOrder</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#Ring\">Ring</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Star/Basic.html#StarRing\">StarRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <spa